e between posting an opinion and causing conflicts. Keep in mind that we are all here to have fun and want to promote a safe and inviting atmosphere. This goes for our message boards and those of other sites.<br>6. Self Removal From The Guild - In order to prevent revolving door policies and the use of de-guilding one's self to express disapproval for any type of issue, any person who remove themselves from the guild will not be allowed to return unless it is approved by a unanimous vote of the Officers. In the case of an accident or a bug that results in the loss of your tag, please contact an officer and let them know what has happened so that they can rectify the situation.<br>7. Loot in guild only events - In the special case of guild events, you will only be permitted to roll or be granted an item if you can benefit from the item in question. If all members present already possess the item, then all will be given a fair chance to roll, or if guild coffers need to be supplied, the item may be sold at market value. <br>8. Unsociable activities such as Kill Stealing, Power Looting, and greed are not allowed. If these are activities you partake in then Oracles of Truth is not the guild for you. All instances of such will result in review and action as deemed appropriate by the Emperial Council.<br>Be sure to help others in need. As a family we should back each other up and helping non-guild members furthers the good name of the guild.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uthundorrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThundorRain  </A> at: 5/29/02 9:54:24 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub54.ezboard.com/foraclesoftruthfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=3.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub54.ezboard.com/foraclesoftruthfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr